DWL Keybind Cheatsheet (Super + /)

Window Management
-----------------
Mod Enter                  → Open terminal (kitty)
Mod d                      → Launch application menu (rofi -show drun)
Mod e                      → Open file manager (thunar)
Mod b                      → Open browser (xdg-open http://)
Mod m                      → Quick Launch Mpv player with highlighted/copied link (quickmpv)
Mod v                      → Clipboard manager (cliphist-rofi)
Mod n                      → Dismiss notifications (makoctl dismiss -a)
Mod a                      → Define word (define)
Mod Shift + S              → Screenshot region (snip)
Mod F5                     → Restart kanshi & enable adaptive-sync
Mod Right                  → Focus next window
Mod Left                   → Focus previous window
Mod Shift + B              → Toggle status bar
Mod i                      → Increase master area windows
Mod p                      → Decrease master area windows
Mod h                      → Shrink window horizontally
Mod l                      → Expand window horizontally
Alt Tab                    → Switch to previous workspace
Mod Shift + A              → Toggle gaps
Mod q                      → Close focused window
Mod f                      → Toggle fullscreen
Mod Ctrl + Space           → Set previous layout
Mod Ctrl + t/f/m           → Set tiling / floating / monocle layout
Mod Shift + Space          → Toggle floating
Mod 0                      → View all Workspaces / tags
Mod Shift + )              → Tag all windows

Workspaces / Tags
-----------------
Mod 1..9                   → Switch to workspace 1..9
Mod Shift + 1..9           → Move focused window to workspace 1..9
Mod Ctrl + 1..9            → Toggle workspace view
Mod Ctrl + Shift + 1..9    → Toggle window tag on workspace

Power / System
--------------
Ctrl Alt + p               → Power menu (kitty -e powermenu)
Ctrl Alt + Backspace  	   → Quit DWL
Ctrl Alt + Fx       	   → Switch VT (1..12)

Mouse
-----
Left click on layout symbol  → Set layout
Right click on layout symbol → Set layout
Middle click on title bar    → Swap windows around (zoom)
Middle click on DISK/RAM/CPU/TIME    → Open terminal
Mod + click on client      → Move/resize window (Left = move, Right = resize, Middle = toggle floating)
Click on tag bar           → Switch/toggle tags
